-- Intesa Sanpaolo May Consider Eastern European Acquisitions, Reuters Says
-- B y   F r a n c e s c a   C i n e l l i
-- 2010-10-16T17:09:16Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-16/intesa-sanpaolo-may-consider-eastern-european-acquisitions-reuters-says.html
Intesa Sanpaolo SpA  may consider
acquisitions in eastern Europe if opportunities arise, Reuters
reported today, citing Chief Executive Officer  Corrado Passera 
in Cernobbio, Italy.  Passera declined to comment on whether Italy’s second-
biggest bank would consider buying assets  UniCredit SpA , Italy’s
biggest lender, may sell in the region, Reuters said.  Passera also reiterated his bank’s commitment to listing
its asset-management unit Banca Fideuram SpA, adding that the
timing of the deal will be determined by markets, Reuters
reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Francesca Cinelli  in Milan at 
 fcinelli@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Merritt at   dmerritt1@bloomberg.net  